window.EQ_DATA["ABNB"] = {"ticker": "ABNB", "meta": {"ticker": "ABNB", "nome_empresa": "Airbnb, Inc.", "setor": "Travel / Marketplace / Internet", "geografia": "US", "moeda_reporte": "USD", "market_cap_usd_bn": "~85", "shares_outstanding_bn": "~0.61 (Class A; total ~0.63 com B)", "fiscal_year_end": "31 de dezembro", "tags": ["setor/internet", "setor/travel", "setor/marketplace", "geografia/us", "moat/rede", "moat/marca", "status/posicao"], "status_tese": "posicao", "data_criacao": "2026-04-28", "ultima_atualizacao": "2026-05-08"}, "views": {"ov": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h1>ABNB — Airbnb, Inc.</h1>\n<blockquote><strong>One-liner</strong>: Marketplace global #1 de short-term rentals — conecta hosts (~5mn listings em 100k+ cidades) a guests (&gt;2bn check-ins históricos). Modelo asset-light com <strong>take rate ~13-14%</strong> sobre GBV, FCF margin ~40%+, e brand sinônima da categoria. <strong>Posição no Etna Off</strong>: 4,2% NAV (status posicao).</blockquote></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>O negócio</h2><h3>O que a empresa faz</h3>\n<p>Airbnb é um <strong>marketplace two-sided</strong> que conecta:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Hosts</strong> (anfitriões) — pessoas que listam acomodações (apartamentos, casas, espaços únicos) ou experiências</li><li><strong>Guests</strong> (hóspedes) — viajantes que reservam estadias ou experiências</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Não é dono de inventário</strong> (asset-light). Cobra <strong>service fee ~14-15%</strong> sobre o booking (split entre host fee ~3% e guest fee ~14%, equivalendo a take rate consolidada ~13-14%).</p>\n<p><strong>Fundada 2008</strong> por Brian Chesky, Joe Gebbia e Nathan Blecharczyk em San Francisco. <strong>IPO Dezembro 2020</strong> ($46bn market cap em IPO).</p>\n<h3>Escala (FY24 actuals — preencher com FY25 quando 10-K estiver no vault)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th>FY25 (a confirmar)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Nights &amp; Experiences booked</td><td>448mn</td><td>~490mn</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Gross Booking Value (GBV, $bn)</td><td>73,3</td><td>~81</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Revenue ($bn)</td><td>9,9</td><td>11,1</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Adjusted EBITDA ($bn)</td><td>3,7</td><td>4,0+</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Adj EBITDA margin</td><td>37%</td><td>~36%</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>FCF ($bn)</td><td>3,8</td><td>~4,5</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>FCF margin</td><td>38%</td><td>~40%</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Active listings (mn)</td><td>7,7</td><td>~8</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Cash + investments ($bn)</td><td>10,6</td><td>~11</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Buyback FY ($bn)</td><td>2,5</td><td>~3+</td><td>—</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Segmentação</h3>\n<p><strong>Por geografia (FY24 approx):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>North America: ~45% revenue</li><li>EMEA: ~30%</li><li>Latin America: ~10%</li><li>Asia Pacific: ~15%</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Asia Pacific + LatAm</strong> são os mercados de maior crescimento (penetração ainda baixa).</p>\n<p><strong>Por tipo de stay:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Short-term rentals (vasta maioria)</li><li>Long-term stays (&gt;28 dias) — ~17-20% das booked nights, growing post-COVID com remote work</li><li>Experiences — relançadas em May/2025 com nova plataforma</li></ul>\n<h3>Take rate breakdown</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Service fee total</strong>: ~14-15% do booking value</li><li>Split típico: ~14% paid by guest + ~3% paid by host = ~17% bruto, mas líquido após taxes/processing ~13-14%</li><li>Take rate vem subindo levemente com mix shift (cross-border + experiences)</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Management</h2><ul><li><strong>CEO + Founder</strong>: Brian Chesky — controla stake significativo, alinhado long-term, ativamente envolvido em produto</li><li><strong>Co-founders ainda envolvidos</strong>: Joe Gebbia (board), Nathan Blecharczyk (Chief Strategy Officer)</li><li><strong>CFO</strong>: Ellie Mertz (desde 2023, antes VP Finance)</li><li><strong>Head of Hosting</strong>: Catherine Powell</li><li><strong>Class B shares</strong>: founders mantêm controle de voto</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Growth drivers</h2><h3>1. International expansion (especialmente Asia + LatAm)</h3>\n<ul><li>Brand awareness ainda &lt;50% em mercados-chave (vs 90%+ em US/UK/FR)</li><li>Penetration de alternative accommodations cresce</li><li>Investment focado em product localization, payments, listings supply</li></ul>\n<h3>2. Experiences relaunch (May/2025)</h3>\n<ul><li>Plataforma reformulada após primeiro experimento (2016) que foi descontinuado</li><li>Targeting marketplace de in-destination experiences</li><li>Optionality alta — TAM grande mas execução incerta</li></ul>\n<h3>3. Services launch (2025)</h3>\n<ul><li>Novo segmento: serviços para hosts/guests (cleaning, photography, etc.)</li><li>Take rate plays — Airbnb captura mais wallet share por reserva</li></ul>\n<h3>4. ADR + nights growth</h3>\n<ul><li>ADR (Average Daily Rate) crescendo modestamente</li><li>Nights crescendo digit-único alto</li></ul>\n<h3>5. Long-term stays (28+ days)</h3>\n<ul><li>~17-20% das nights, +20% YoY</li><li>Beneficiário de remote/hybrid work permanence</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Catalisadores</h2><ul><li><strong>Aceleração internacional</strong> especialmente Asia-Pacific (Japão, Korea pós-Olympics, India/SE Asia)</li><li><strong>Experiences traction</strong> — primeira leitura material em 2026</li><li><strong>Services revenue</strong> — primeiros números em earnings calls FY26</li><li><strong>Buyback acelerado</strong> em correções de mercado</li><li><strong>Margin expansion</strong> via mix shift cross-border + ad load (host ads)</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Financeiros (snapshot FY24 - preencher com FY25 após 10-K)</h2><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue ($bn)</td><td>9,9</td><td>11,1</td><td>+12%</td></tr><tr><td>Gross Margin</td><td>82%</td><td>83%</td><td>+1pp</td></tr><tr><td>Op Margin (GAAP)</td><td>18%</td><td>~21%</td><td>+300bps</td></tr><tr><td>Adj EBITDA Margin</td><td>37%</td><td>~36%</td><td>-100bps</td></tr><tr><td>FCF Margin</td><td>38%</td><td>~40%</td><td>+200bps</td></tr><tr><td>Net Income (GAAP, $bn)</td><td>4,8</td><td>~2,7</td><td>(boomerang de tax benefit FY23)</td></tr><tr><td>EPS Diluted (GAAP)</td><td>7,2</td><td>~4,1</td><td>normalização</td></tr><tr><td>Cash + investments ($bn)</td><td>10,6</td><td>~11</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Buyback ($bn)</td><td>2,5</td><td>~3</td><td>—</td></tr></tbody></table></div></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Posição no portfolio</h2><p>Update <strong>2026-04-28</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=portfolio\" title=\"portfolio/portfolio\">portfolio.md</a>:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>6.576 ações</strong> @ entry $141,87</li><li><strong>% NAV: 4,2%</strong> (entre as menores posições G7)</li><li><strong>Performance vs entry: +0,67%</strong> (recém-aberta ou flat)</li><li>Status: <strong>posicao</strong></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Sizing comentário</strong>: peso 4,2% é menor que outras G7 do portfolio (NVDA 16,5%, GOOGL 23,9%, etc.). Indica conviction moderada / starter position.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 — first quarter post-FY25 + debt refinancing</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-08</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">10-Q SEC accession 0001559720-26-000014</a> (40 páginas, OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime — text layer scrambled). Period ended 31-Mar-2026.</p>\n<h3>Headline metrics Q1 FY26</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>Q1 FY26</strong></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$2,272M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$2,678M</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+18%</strong> ← beat guidance ($2.59-2.63B = +14-16%)</td></tr><tr><td>Income from operations</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$38M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$86M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+126%</td></tr><tr><td>Op margin</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.7%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">3.2%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+1.5pp</td></tr><tr><td>Net income</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$154M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$160M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+4%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Adj EBITDA</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$417M</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$519M</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+24%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Adj EBITDA margin</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">18%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>19%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+1pp</td></tr><tr><td><strong>OCF</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$1,789M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$1,708M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-4.5%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FCF</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$1,781M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$1,704M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-4.3%</td></tr><tr><td>FCF margin</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">78%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">64%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>-1,400bps</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Diluted EPS</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$0.24</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$0.26</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+8%</td></tr><tr><td>Tax rate</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">11%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>43%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+32pp</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Operating metrics</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>Q1 FY26</strong></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Nights &amp; Seats Booked (M)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">143</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>156</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+9%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>GBV ($M)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$24,515</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$29,187</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+19%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Implied take rate (rev/GBV)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">9.27%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">9.18%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-9bps</td></tr><tr><td>ADR implícito</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$171</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$187</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+9%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ <strong>Nights/Seats Booked +9% acelera levemente</strong> vs FY25 +8% full-year. <strong>GBV +19%</strong> = ADR + nights crescendo juntos.</p>\n<h3>Geographic — North America desacelera, internacional acelera</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Região</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY25 ($M)</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26 ($M)</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>North America</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1,054</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1,138</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+8%</strong> ← slowing (FY25 Q4 era +12%)</td></tr><tr><td>EMEA</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">597</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">747</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+25%</strong> ← acelerando (FX boost)</td></tr><tr><td>LatAm</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">343</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">451</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+31%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>APAC</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">278</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">342</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+23%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>2,272</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>2,678</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+18%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Mix shift</strong>: NA caiu de 46.4% Q1 25 → 42.5% Q1 26. International expansion thesis se materializando.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 NOVO no 10-Q (não no shareholder letter): $2.5B Senior Notes — primeiro debt material no balance sheet</strong></h3>\n<p>Em <strong>16-Mar-2026</strong>, ABNB emitiu <strong>$2.5B em Senior Unsecured Notes</strong> em 3 tranches:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Tranche</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Coupon</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Eff Rate</th><th>Maturity</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>2029 Notes</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>4.40%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">4.7%</td><td>March 2029</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$850M</td></tr><tr><td>2031 Notes</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>4.65%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">4.9%</td><td>March 2031</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$850M</td></tr><tr><td>2036 Notes</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>5.25%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.4%</td><td>March 2036</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$800M</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">mix</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~4.95% blended</strong></td><td></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$2,500M</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Uso de proceeds</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>$2.0B</strong> para repagar <strong>0% convertible notes due 2026</strong> (que matured neste mesmo trimestre)</li><li><strong>$500M retidos</strong> para general corporate purposes</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Interest rate swap $1.7B notional</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>2031 Notes ($850M) + 2036 Notes ($800M) → swapped fixed→floating SOFR-based</li><li>2029 Notes mantém fixo 4.40%</li><li>ABNB recebe fixo, paga SOFR + spread</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Implicação estrutural</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>ABNB sai de <strong>0% converts (potencialmente dilutivos)</strong> para <strong>plain vanilla unsecured (~5% blended)</strong></li><li>Trade-off: <strong>mais cash interest expense</strong> mas <strong>EPS accretive long-term</strong> (sem dilution risk)</li><li>$500M extra na BS pra optionality de M&amp;A ou buyback acelerado</li><li>2022 Credit Facility $1B unsecured ainda intacta (no draws)</li><li>Total LT debt agora $2,475M (de $0 pré-Q1 — converts eram current portion)</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Tax provision jump $19M → $121M (+537%)</strong></h3>\n<p>Driver: <strong>$69M one-time CAMT adjustment</strong> de deferred tax assets devido a:</p>\n<ol><li>Mudanças no U.S. Corporate Alternative Minimum Tax</li><li>Decreased SBC tax deductions</li></ol>\n<p>Effective rate: <strong>11% Q1 25 → 43% Q1 26</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Outlook</strong>: mgmt FY25 guidance era &quot;mid-to-high teens&quot; para 2026+ por OBBBA. Q1 26 a 43% é <strong>muito acima</strong> = FY26 effective rate provavelmente sobe vs Q1 25 11%, mas deve estabilizar abaixo de 30% após one-off.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 IRS dispute $1.3B + penalties + interest — material binary risk</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q Note 10 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-21\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-21\">p.21</a>) detalha:</p>\n<ul><li>IRS auditing tax years <strong>2013, 2016, 2017, 2018</strong></li><li>Primary issue: <strong>valuation of international IP transferred to subsidiary in 2013</strong></li><li>Dec 2020: NOPA (proposed adjustment) de <strong>$1.3B incremental tax + penalties + interest</strong></li><li>Mai 2024: Statutory Notice of Deficiency confirmando posição IRS</li><li>Jul 2024: ABNB petitioned U.S. Tax Court for redetermination</li><li>ABNB believes &quot;adequate amounts have been reserved&quot; mas se IRS prevails, <strong>material adverse impact</strong> em financial position + cash flow</li></ul>\n<p>→ <strong>Risco binário relevante</strong> que o mercado parece descontar com probabilidade baixa, mas magnitude é material (~$1.3B = ~12% do market cap em case loss).</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Other contingencies — non-income tax matters</strong></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Lodging tax obligations payable</strong>: $387M (Mar/26 = Dec/25 — flat)</li><li><strong>Estimated lodging tax probable losses</strong>: $114M → $131M (+$17M Q1)</li><li><strong>Other non-income tax matters reasonably possible loss</strong>: <strong>$195-215M</strong> acima do accrued</li></ul>\n<p>→ Total contingencies não accrued: ~<strong>$200-215M</strong> (ex-IRS dispute) = ~2% do market cap.</p>\n<h3>Other one-offs Q1 26</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>+$70M realized gain</strong> na venda de equity investment (acquired by 3rd party) — non-recurring, em Other income</li><li><strong>Spain fine for STR non-compliance</strong> (Sep/2025) — number truncado no OCR mas registrado</li></ul>\n<h3>Capital allocation — buyback acelerando</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>Q1 FY26</strong></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Repurchases ($M)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$807</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$1,088</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+35%</td></tr><tr><td>Shares retired (M)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">6.1</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>8.1</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+33%</td></tr><tr><td>Avg price</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$132</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$134</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+2%</td></tr><tr><td>Remaining authorization (Mar/26)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$4.5B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Annualized rate ~$4.4B</strong> (vs FY25 ~$4B). Continua acima do FCF generation = continued cash deployment.</p>\n<p><strong>Shares outstanding</strong>: 619M (Mar/25) → 595M (Mar/26) = <strong>-24M shares (-3.9%)</strong> em 12 meses.</p>\n<h3>SBC continua acelerando (não em linha com guidance)</h3>\n<ul><li>Q1 26 SBC: <strong>$410M (+15% YoY)</strong> vs $358M Q1 25</li><li>Mgmt guidance Q4 25 letter: &quot;growth rate of SBC and headcount lower than 2025&quot; (FY25 era +13%)</li><li>Q1 26 a +15% <strong>NÃO está cumprindo guidance</strong> — watch nos próximos quarters</li></ul>\n<h3>Forward visibility — bookings collected</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Dec 31, 2025</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Mar 31, 2026</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Δ QoQ</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Funds receivable + held on behalf of customers</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$6,959M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$10,550M</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+$3.59B (+52%)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Unearned fees</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$1,743M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$2,733M</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+$990M (+57%)</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ Booking collected mas não realizadas (receita futura) <strong>explodiram QoQ</strong>. Sazonalidade típica Q1 (peak booking pré-summer travel) mas magnitude reforça <strong>forward visibility positiva</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Macro commentary (10-Q MD&amp;A)</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;The conflict in the Middle East has had and is expected to continue to have a slight impact on near-term booking trends, including increased cancellations in Europe, the Middle East, and Africa (&quot;EMEA&quot;) and Asia Pacific.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Mgmt explicit sobre <strong>EMEA + APAC headwind moderado</strong> do conflito Middle East. Mas growth ainda foi +25% / +23% nessas regiões (FX boost compensando).</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We observed a lengthening of lead times across all regions, driven in part by the continued expansion of our deferred payment programs.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ <strong>Reserve Now Pay Later</strong> (lançado em US Q4 25 com &gt;70% adoption) está sendo <strong>expandida globalmente</strong> = boost de booking conversion + lead times mais longos = <strong>forward visibility melhor</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Implicações para tese (delta vs Q4 25 / pré 10-Q)</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>Top-line momentum forte</strong>: Q1 26 +18% vs guide +14-16% = beat ✓ <strong>Adj EBITDA margin 19% (vs 18%)</strong> — slight expansion mesmo com investimentos ✓ <strong>GBV +19% / Nights +9%</strong> = ADR expansion + nights growth combined ✓ <strong>International expansion materializando</strong>: EMEA +25%, LatAm +31%, APAC +23% ✓ <strong>Forward visibility forte</strong>: unearned fees +57% QoQ, funds payable +52% QoQ ✓ <strong>Capital structure shift</strong>: convert 0% → unsecured ~5% blended, removed dilution risk ✓ <strong>Buyback acelerando</strong>: $1.1B Q1, $4.4B run rate, $4.5B authorization remaining ⚠️ <strong>NA slowing (+8%)</strong> — primary market deceleration; pode ser pressão estrutural ou TAM saturation ⚠️ <strong>FCF margin caiu de 78% → 64%</strong> — sazonal (Q1 normalmente alto por unearned fees) mas magnitude vale watch ⚠️ <strong>Tax rate Q1 a 43%</strong> vs guidance &quot;mid-to-high teens&quot; = FY26 effective rate vai estar elevado ⚠️ <strong>SBC +15% YoY</strong> — não respondeu disciplina prometida (guide era &quot;lower than 2025&quot;) ⚠️ <strong>IRS $1.3B dispute</strong> + Spain fine + non-income tax exposure ~$200M = total binary tail risk material</p>\n<h3>Cross-implications</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=BKNG\" title=\"wiki/BKNG\">BKNG</a> (futura) — comparar Q1 FY26 BKNG quando ingerido. ABNB mostra que internacional está acelerando = pode ser tema cross-OTA</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — não diretamente; mas Reserve Now Pay Later usa AI-style targeting + customer support automation (Chesky disclosed em FY25 calls)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> — ABNB AI customer support rolled out 1/3 issues sem agente humano = aplicação prática agentic AI no consumer-facing layer</li></ul></section>\n<details class=\"notes-appendix\"><summary>Notas, pendências e changelog</summary><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Pontos em aberto / a investigar</h2><ul><li>[ ] <strong>10-K FY24 + FY25</strong> — usuário vai colocar em F:\\...\\Airbnb\\10Ks\\</li><li>[ ] <strong>FY25 actuals consolidados</strong> (revenue, EBITDA, FCF, listings, GBV)</li><li>[ ] <strong>Experiences relaunch traction</strong> — números em FY25 calls</li><li>[ ] <strong>Services revenue split</strong> — ainda pequeno mas growing</li><li>[ ] <strong>Comparativo head-to-head com BKNG STR</strong> — share, mix, take rate</li><li>[ ] <strong>Long-term stays mix evolution</strong> — % of nights FY23/FY24/FY25</li><li>[ ] <strong>Cohort economics</strong> — guest LTV, host retention by tenure</li><li>[ ] <strong>Pershing Square 2023 challenge thesis</strong> — <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2023-04-Pershing-Square-Challenge\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/2023-04-Pershing-Square-Challenge\">2023-04-Pershing-Square-Challenge</a> (no vault, processar)</li><li>[ ] <strong>Bernstein initiation</strong> — <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Bernstein-Initiation\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/Bernstein-Initiation\">Bernstein-Initiation</a> (no vault, processar)</li><li>[ ] <strong>Wells Fargo Apr/2026</strong> — <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-Wells\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/2026-04-Wells\">2026-04-Wells</a> (no vault, processar)</li><li>[ ] <strong>AirDNA Global STR Oct/2025</strong> — supply/demand data (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-10-AirDNA-BoA\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/2025-10-AirDNA-BoA\">2025-10-AirDNA-BoA</a>)</li><li>[ ] <strong>Rodar Perguntas 1-4</strong> quando vault estiver populado</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Histórico de atualizações</h2><ul><li><strong>2026-05-08</strong> (later): ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 shareholder letter + earnings call ingeridos</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter\">FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter</a> 27 páginas + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> 20 páginas FactSet, ambos OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime). Adicionada nova seção &quot;Q1 FY26 — strategic narrative&quot; com material <strong>NÃO</strong> capturado no 10-Q. <strong>Achados materiais</strong>: (1) <strong>🔥 FY26 OUTLOOK RAISED — primeira vez em multi anos</strong>: Nights &amp; Seats Booked <strong>low-to-mid teens (~12-15%) vs FY25 +8% = 4-7pp acceleration</strong>; Adj EBITDA Margin &quot;at least 35%&quot;; effective tax rate &quot;high teens&quot; (down de 20% FY25); (2) <strong>🔥 Reserve Now Pay Later = 20% do GBV global Q1 26</strong> (era &gt;70% adoption só US Q4 25; agora rolled out globally); drives lead times longer + larger/higher-priced homes; net positive em todos mercados testados; ainda em &quot;early innings&quot; (rollout desktop + merchandising up-funnel pendentes); (3) <strong>App-first momentum</strong>: nights booked via app <strong>+22% YoY</strong>, <strong>63% do total</strong> (vs 58%) — &quot;strongest in a decade&quot;; (4) <strong>First-time bookers +10% YoY = highest desde Q1 22</strong>: Brazil origin nights +22% (3rd consecutive Q), India origin nights <strong>+50% YoY</strong> (first-time bookers India +75%+!), expansion markets +2x core; 16 local marketing campaigns Q1 alone; (5) <strong>🔥 Major events strategy</strong>: Olympics Milano Cortina (Q1) — 200k guests, GBV +3x in Milan, supply +30%; <strong>FIFA World Cup 2026 será o maior evento da história ABNB</strong> com &gt;100k novos listings em 16 cidades (Paris precedent: 50%+ supply retention 6mo pós-games); (6) <strong>🔥 AI ROI quantificado</strong>: 60% do código authored by AI (vs 30% industry = 2x); 40%+ customer support resolution sem humano (vs 33% Q4); <strong>cost-per-booking -10% YoY em Q1</strong> (primeira quantificação P&amp;L); (7) <strong>🔥 New CTO Ahmad</strong> (former leader Meta Llama model) — major hire para AI-native infrastructure; (8) <strong>AI Search ainda em exploration mode</strong>; Brian crítico explícito do chatbot model (4 problemas: too much text, no direct manipulation, comparison broken, multiplayer); (9) <strong>Hotels potential</strong>: &lt;single-digit% nights atual mas all top-line metrics scaling; <strong>55% de hotel bookers depois reservam home</strong> = onboarding ramp; hotels prefer ABNB economics (30%+ lower commissions vs OTAs); independents pressionados a franchise vs ABNB alternativa; &quot;multi-billion dollar revenue business&quot; potential; mais updates <strong>May 20 Summer Release</strong>; (10) <strong>Delta partnership expandida</strong> para Experiences + Services (1 mile/$ stays + 3 miles/$ Experiences); revenue share program; sem in-house loyalty announced ainda (Brian: &quot;best loyalty is people loving the product&quot;); flights &quot;on the table for future vision&quot;; (11) <strong>Amazon-as-inspiration framing</strong> (Brian to MS): &quot;ecosystem&quot;, each new offering 10% different = compounding efficiency; hybrid 1st-party (unique to ABNB) + 3rd-party (Instacart for grocery); implied verticals coming: air, car service, grocery, agentic; (12) <strong>🔥 S&amp;P + Moody&#x27;s upgraded ABNB to Investment Grade</strong>: $2.5B notes issued at IG rates; <strong>first IG-rated debt</strong> = structural milestone; (13) <strong>PMS host single fee migration</strong>: agora <strong>&gt;1/4 das active listings</strong> sob single 15.5% fee; (14) <strong>Guest travel insurance revenue +45% YoY</strong> — material; available 12 largest countries; (15) <strong>Q2 FY26 guide</strong>: Revenue $3.04B (+14-16% incl ~3% FX), Nights slight deceleration vs Q1 (~100bps ME headwind), Adj EBITDA + margin up YoY. <strong>Implicação principal</strong>: tese se confirma e ACELERA — combined raise (nights low-to-mid teens + take rate up + AI cost -10%) sugere FY26 revenue/EPS path materially above FOX modelo $13.76B/$4.61. <strong>Cross-link</strong>: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> (AI customer support real-world validation), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> (ecosystem strategy framing inspiration).</li><li><strong>2026-05-08</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 10-Q ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> — SEC accession 0001559720-26-000014, 40 páginas, OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime). Adicionada nova seção &quot;Q1 FY26 — first quarter post-FY25 + debt refinancing&quot;. <strong>Disclosures materiais</strong>: (1) <strong>Revenue Q1 $2,678M (+18% YoY) = beat guidance</strong> ($2.59-2.63B = +14-16%); (2) <strong>Adj EBITDA $519M (+24%), margin 19% (+1pp)</strong>; (3) <strong>Nights &amp; Seats +9%, GBV +19%, ADR +9%</strong>; (4) <strong>Geographic mix shift</strong>: NA slowing (+8%) vs EMEA +25%, LatAm +31%, APAC +23% — international expansion materializando; (5) <strong>🔥 $2.5B Senior Unsecured Notes issued 16-Mar-2026</strong> ($850M @ 4.40% 2029 + $850M @ 4.65% 2031 + $800M @ 5.25% 2036, blended ~5%) — repaid $2B 0% converts due 2026, retained $500M; <strong>$1.7B notional interest rate swap fixed→floating SOFR</strong> (2031+2036); capital structure shift do convert (potentially dilutive) para plain vanilla unsecured (EPS accretive long-term); (6) <strong>Tax provision jump $19M → $121M</strong> ($69M one-time CAMT adjustment), effective rate 11% → 43%; (7) <strong>$70M one-off gain</strong> sale equity investment (non-recurring, in Other income); (8) <strong>IRS dispute $1.3B + penalties + interest</strong> sobre 2013 IP transfer — Statutory Notice of Deficiency, Tax Court petition Jul/2024 = material binary tail risk; (9) <strong>Buyback Q1 26 $1,088M (+35%)</strong>, 8.1M shares retired, $4.5B remaining authorization, annualized $4.4B; (10) <strong>SBC +15% YoY</strong> vs guide &quot;lower than 2025&quot; = não cumprindo disciplina; (11) <strong>Forward visibility forte</strong>: unearned fees +57% QoQ ($1.74B → $2.73B), funds payable +52% QoQ ($6.96B → $10.55B) — driven by Reserve Now Pay Later global expansion; (12) <strong>Mid East conflict</strong>: slight cancellations EMEA + APAC mas growth ainda +23-25%; (13) <strong>Lodging tax + non-income tax probable losses ~$200-215M</strong> ex-accrued. <strong>Implicação tese</strong>: Q1 valida re-aceleração mas com nuances (NA slowing, tax pressure one-off, SBC discipline pendente). Cross-link com <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> via AI customer support adoption.</li><li><strong>2026-04-28</strong>: wiki criada como skeleton. Conteúdo inicial baseado em conhecimento estrutural sobre Airbnb.</li><li><strong>2026-04-29</strong>: <strong>Fase 1 completa</strong> — 47 docs OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime (~6h CPU): 6 SEC 10-Ks (FY20-FY25) + 20 earnings calls (FY21Q1→FY25Q4) + 21 shareholder letters (FY20Q4→FY25Q4). Wiki enriquecida com seção &quot;Evolução histórica FY20→FY25&quot; com headline financials, operational KPIs, trajetória de revenue (re-aceleração Q4 25 para +12%), guidance Q1/FY26 (+14-16% revenue), análise por ano, take rate dynamics, e drivers FY25 (Services launch May/2025, Reserve Now Pay Later &gt;70% adoption Q4, AI support 1/3 issues sem agente, expansão geográfica 2x core markets).</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Fontes no vault — Fase 1 completa (29-Apr-2026)</h2><h3>SEC 10-Ks (6 docs)</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY20-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY20-10-K\">FY20-10-K</a> — IPO year (filed Feb/2021)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-10-K\">FY21-10-K</a> — full COVID recovery</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a> — full bounce-back +75%</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a> — Year of Efficiency, IPO buyback start</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a> — mid-cycle plateau</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> — re-acceleration via Services + AI</li></ul>\n<h3>SEC 10-Q — <em>ingested 2026-05-08</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> — Q1 FY26 (period ended 31-Mar-2026) — <strong>Revenue $2.68B +18% beat, $2.5B Senior Notes issued (refinanced 0% convert), $1.3B IRS dispute, NA slowing / int&#x27;l accelerating, Adj EBITDA margin 19%, buyback $1.09B</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Shareholder letters &amp; earnings calls — <em>Q1 FY26 ingested 2026-05-08</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter\">FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter</a> — Q1 FY26 (release pré-10-Q) — <strong>🔥 FY26 outlook raised: nights low-to-mid teens; Adj EBITDA margin ≥35%; AI cost-per-booking -10%; RNPL 20% global GBV; Olympics 200k guests; World Cup &gt;100k new listings; hotels &quot;multi-billion dollar potential&quot;; Amazon-as-inspiration ecosystem framing; S&amp;P + Moody&#x27;s IG upgrade</strong></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> — FactSet Corrected Transcript (07-May-2026, 20 páginas) — Brian Chesky + Ellie Mertz Q&amp;A com Citi, Bernstein, Oppenheimer, Wells Fargo, BNP, MS, Goldman, Jefferies, Mizuho, Baird, JPMorgan</li></ul>\n<h3>Earnings Calls (20 docs)</h3>\n<ul><li>FY21: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q2-earnings-call\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q3-earnings-call\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4</a></li><li>FY22: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q2-earnings-call\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q3-earnings-call\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4</a></li><li>FY23: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q2-earnings-call\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q3-earnings-call\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4</a></li><li>FY24: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q2-earnings-call\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q3-earnings-call\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4</a></li><li>FY25: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q1-earnings-call\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q2-earnings-call\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q3-earnings-call\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4</a></li></ul>\n<h3>Shareholder Letters (21 docs)</h3>\n<ul><li>FY20: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY20-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY20-Q4-shareholder-letter\">Q4</a></li><li>FY21: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q1-shareholder-letter\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q2-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q2-shareholder-letter\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q3-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q3-shareholder-letter\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY21-Q4-shareholder-letter\">Q4</a></li><li>FY22: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q1-shareholder-letter\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q2-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q2-shareholder-letter\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q3-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q3-shareholder-letter\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY22-Q4-shareholder-letter\">Q4</a></li><li>FY23: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q1-shareholder-letter\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q2-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q2-shareholder-letter\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q3-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q3-shareholder-letter\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY23-Q4-shareholder-letter\">Q4</a></li><li>FY24: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q1-shareholder-letter\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q2-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q2-shareholder-letter\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q3-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q3-shareholder-letter\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY24-Q4-shareholder-letter\">Q4</a></li><li>FY25: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q1-shareholder-letter\">Q1</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q2-shareholder-letter\">Q2</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q3-shareholder-letter\">Q3</a> · <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q4-shareholder-letter\">Q4</a> <em>(Feb/2026 release)</em></li></ul>\n<h3>Backlog para Fase 2 (research externo, em F:\\...\\Airbnb)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Pershing Square Challenge ABNB</strong> (Apr/2023) — long thesis externa</li><li><strong>Bernstein Initiating Coverage</strong> — sell-side initiation</li><li><strong>Wells Fargo report</strong> (Apr/2026) — recente</li><li><strong>AirDNA Global STR Oct 2025</strong> (BoA) — supply/demand data</li><li><strong>Airbnb Valuation Update</strong> (Jul/2023)</li><li><strong>AI Bull Case OTAS</strong></li><li><strong>CompsTravel.xlsx</strong> — comp set</li><li><strong>ABNB v2.pdf</strong>, <strong>ABNB New.pptx</strong> — material interno</li><li><strong>Bern 2023</strong> — folder com Bernstein research</li><li><strong>Papers</strong> — folder</li><li><strong>Modelo proprietário</strong> ABNB.xlsx (já parte do FOX Stock Guide)</li></ul></section></details>", "ic": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Tese de investimento (provisória — refinar via Pergunta 1 quando vault estiver populado)</h2><ul><li><strong>Compounder asset-light em mercado estrutural</strong>: TAM short-term rentals + alternative accommodations cresce &gt;2x mais rápido que hotelaria tradicional. Airbnb captura ~20% do TAM com runway claro.</li><li><strong>Moat duplo (brand + network)</strong>:<ul><li><strong>Brand</strong>: nome virou verbo (&quot;airbnb it&quot;). Reconhecimento global #1 em alternative accommodations. <strong>~90% do tráfego é direto/non-paid</strong>, brutal vantagem de CAC vs Booking/Expedia</li><li><strong>Network effect two-sided</strong>: hosts atraem guests → reviews acumulam → escolha → mais hosts</li></ul></li><li><strong>FCF machine</strong>: Op margin ~25%+ ajustado, FCF conversion &gt;100%, balance sheet $10bn+ líquido, capital return agressivo via buyback</li><li><strong>Optionality</strong>: Experiences relaunch (May/2025), Services launch, geographic expansion (mercados sub-penetrados), B2B/Travel Tech via Airbnb for Work</li><li><strong>Riscos</strong>: regulação local (NYC, Barcelona, Amsterdam caps), competition (Booking aggressive em STR), takeover via OTAs em saturação, dependência de discretionary travel spend</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Posição atual no Etna Off</strong> (snapshot <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=portfolio\" title=\"portfolio/portfolio\">2026-04-24</a>):</p>\n<ul><li>6.576 ações @ $141,87 (entry)</li><li>Preço d0: $142,82 → +0,67% vs entry</li><li>Notional: $939k = 4,2% do NAV</li><li>Status: posicao</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Vantagem competitiva (moat)</h2><h3>1. Brand &amp; direct traffic — o moat principal</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>&gt;90% do tráfego é direto / unpaid</strong> (não paga Google Ads para a maior parte)</li><li>Compare: Booking gasta ~$7bn/ano em marketing performance (~30% revenue); ABNB gasta ~$2bn (~18% revenue)</li><li>Implicação: <strong>margem estrutural superior</strong> + barreira de entrada gigantesca para wannabes</li></ul>\n<h3>2. Two-sided network effect</h3>\n<ul><li>5mn+ hosts ativos × 8mn+ listings × 2bn+ historical guests</li><li>Reviews acumulam como capital perpétuo (não-replicável)</li><li>Liquidez geográfica: 100k+ cidades, 220+ países</li></ul>\n<h3>3. Asset-light + capital efficiency</h3>\n<ul><li>Não opera nem possui inventário</li><li>ROIC alto via marketplace economics</li><li>FCF conversion ~100%+ permite buyback agressivo</li></ul>\n<h3>4. Data + ML moat</h3>\n<ul><li>Pricing optimization (Smart Pricing)</li><li>Search + ranking (matching guest preferences ↔ host listings)</li><li>Trust &amp; safety (fraud detection, scam prevention)</li></ul>\n<h3>5. Regulatory acumen</h3>\n<ul><li>Time global de policy/government affairs</li><li>Acordos com cidades (tax collection, host limits, data sharing)</li><li>Switching cost regulatório: novos entrantes precisam construir esses acordos do zero</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Riscos</h2><h3>1. Regulação local</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>NYC</strong>: Local Law 18 (2023) reduziu listings drásticamente — modelo de &quot;permanente vs temporário&quot; forçado</li><li><strong>Barcelona, Paris, Amsterdam, Tokyo</strong>: caps em listings/nights por host</li><li>Risco de cascading: cada cidade vira precedente</li><li>Mitigante: &lt;2% revenue de qualquer cidade individual</li></ul>\n<h3>2. Competition</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Booking.com</strong>: aggressive em short-term rentals nos últimos 3 anos. ~3-4mn properties STR (mas mix de hotels/STR menor)</li><li><strong>Expedia (Vrbo)</strong>: focado em US whole-home (família grande, casa de praia)</li><li><strong>Local incumbents</strong>: especialmente em China (não opera), Asia (variados)</li><li>Mitigante: ABNB tem brand e #1 NPS na categoria</li></ul>\n<h3>3. Macro / discretionary travel</h3>\n<ul><li>Recessão = corte em viagens (especialmente leisure long-haul)</li><li>2023 mostrou resilience (+18% nights vs 2022) mas próxima recessão é teste real</li><li>Long-term stays + business travel agem como estabilizadores</li></ul>\n<h3>4. Host churn / supply</h3>\n<ul><li>Costs of hosting subindo (mortgage rates, regulação)</li><li>Some hosts saindo da plataforma</li><li>Mitigante: net listings ainda crescendo</li></ul>\n<h3>5. Take rate ceiling</h3>\n<ul><li>Take rate ~14-15% já é high vs marketplaces puros</li><li>Tentativas de subir podem causar host backlash</li><li>Recurso para growth: ATTACH new revenue (services, experiences) sem subir core take</li></ul></section>", "val": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Valuation (snapshot)</h2><ul><li><strong>P/E FY26E</strong>: ~30x (EPS ~$5)</li><li><strong>EV/EBITDA FY26E</strong>: ~22x</li><li><strong>FCF Yield FY26E</strong>: ~4,5%</li><li><strong>Histórico 3Y avg</strong>: P/E 35-40x; valuation comprimiu em 2024-2025 com worries de growth deceleration</li><li><strong>vs peers</strong>:<ul><li>Booking (BKNG): P/E ~22x — desconto justificado por mix mais commoditizado</li><li>Expedia (EXPE): P/E ~12x — desconto por estrutura mista, brand fragmentado</li></ul></li><li><strong>Implicação</strong>: ABNB negocia em prêmio adequado pelo perfil compounder; downside relativo limitado se manter +10% revenue growth</li></ul></section>", "pa": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Historical Price Action</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/ABNB.md</code>.</p></div>", "er": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Evolução histórica — retrospectiva FY20 → FY25</h2><p>Adicionada <strong>2026-04-29</strong> via ingestão de <strong>47 docs primários OCR&#x27;d</strong>: 6 10-Ks (FY20-FY25) + 20 earnings calls (FY21 Q1 → FY25 Q4) + 21 shareholder letters (FY20 Q4 → FY25 Q4). Pipeline rapidocr-onnxruntime, ~6h CPU total.</p>\n<h3>Headline Financials (FY25 actual via Q4 letter + 10-K)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th><strong>FY25</strong></th><th>YoY 24→25</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Revenue ($bn)</strong></td><td>9.917</td><td>11.102</td><td><strong>12.241</strong></td><td><strong>+10%</strong> (10% ex-FX)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Adj EBITDA ($bn)</strong></td><td>3.7</td><td>~4.1</td><td><strong>4.3</strong></td><td>+5%</td></tr><tr><td>Adj EBITDA margin</td><td>37%</td><td>36%</td><td><strong>35%</strong></td><td>-100bps</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Net Income ($bn)</strong></td><td>4.792 (incl tax benefit)</td><td>~2.6</td><td><strong>2.5</strong></td><td>-4% (one-off CAMT $213M)</td></tr><tr><td>Net margin</td><td>48%</td><td>23%</td><td><strong>21%</strong></td><td>normalização</td></tr><tr><td><strong>GAAP EPS diluted</strong></td><td>7.24</td><td>4.11</td><td>~3.85</td><td>-6%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FCF ($bn)</strong></td><td>3.8</td><td>~4.5</td><td><strong>4.6</strong></td><td>+2%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FCF margin</strong></td><td>38%</td><td>41%</td><td><strong>38%</strong></td><td>-300bps</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Op Cash Flow ($bn)</strong></td><td>3.9</td><td>~4.5</td><td><strong>4.6</strong></td><td>flat</td></tr><tr><td>Effective tax rate</td><td>n/a</td><td>n/a</td><td>20% (incl. one-off)</td><td>guidance &quot;mid-to-high teens&quot; 2026+ por OBBBA</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Buyback FY ($bn)</strong></td><td>2.5</td><td>~3.4</td><td>~4</td><td>acelerando</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Operational metrics (key business KPIs)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th><strong>FY25</strong></th><th>YoY 24→25</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Nights &amp; Seats Booked (mn)</strong></td><td>448</td><td>~492</td><td><strong>533.0</strong></td><td><strong>+8%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>GBV ($bn)</strong></td><td>73.3</td><td>~81.8</td><td><strong>91.3</strong></td><td><strong>+12%</strong> (10% ex-FX)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ADR ($)</strong></td><td>~166</td><td>~166</td><td>~171</td><td>+3% (price + FX + mix)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Implied take rate</strong></td><td>13.5%</td><td>13.6%</td><td><strong>13.4%</strong></td><td>-20bps (Q4 13.6% mas FY full year ~13.4%)</td></tr><tr><td>Active listings (mn)</td><td>7.7</td><td>~8.0</td><td>~8.4</td><td>+5%</td></tr><tr><td>Cash + investments ($bn)</td><td>10.6</td><td>~11.3</td><td>~11.5</td><td>flat</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Q4 2025 specifics (released Feb/2026)</h3>\n<p><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY25-Q4-shareholder-letter\">FY25-Q4-shareholder-letter</a>:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Revenue Q4: $2.778bn (+12% YoY)</strong> — exceeded high end of guidance</li><li><strong>GBV Q4: $20.4bn (+16%, 13% ex-FX)</strong> — accelerating</li><li><strong>Nights &amp; Seats Q4: 121.9mn (+10% YoY)</strong> — strongest growth quarter of the year</li><li><strong>Adj EBITDA Q4: $786mn (+3% YoY) com margin 28%</strong> (vs 31% Q4 24 — pressure por planned investments + $90mn non-income tax matters)</li><li><strong>Net Income Q4: $341mn (margin 12%)</strong> — comprimido por investments + tax matter</li><li><strong>FCF Q4: $521mn (margin 19%)</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Trajetória de revenue — accelerando após mid-cycle slowdown</h3>\n<ul><li>FY21 → FY22: +75% (recovery COVID)</li><li>FY22 → FY23: +18% (normalization)</li><li>FY23 → FY24: +12%</li><li>FY24 → FY25: <strong>+10%</strong> (steady)</li><li><strong>Q4 25 acelerou para +12%</strong> — momentum into 2026</li></ul>\n<h3>Guidance Q1 2026 + FY26</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Q1 2026 revenue: $2.59-2.63bn (+14% a +16% YoY)</strong> — inclui ~3pp FX tailwind</li><li>Implied take rate Q1 2026: up slightly YoY</li><li><strong>FY26 outlook</strong>: &quot;sustained strength in core business + healthy demand + execution em key growth initiatives&quot;</li><li><strong>2026 será de aceleração</strong>, não apenas manutenção — Chesky framing</li></ul>\n<h3>Análise da trajetória (key insights from earnings calls)</h3>\n<h4>FY21 (recovery COVID)</h4>\n<ul><li>Q1: &quot;biggest year in our history&quot; projeção. North America back to 2019 levels in May 2021</li><li>Q3: long-term stays atingiram 20% of total nights</li><li>Q4: brand resilience demonstrated; saving direct traffic &gt;90%</li></ul>\n<h4>FY22 (full recovery)</h4>\n<ul><li>Revenue +75% vs 2019 (full bounce-back)</li><li>ADR record highs por shift to non-urban + larger groups</li><li>Cross-border travel recovery acelerando</li></ul>\n<h4>FY23 (efficiency + product reinvention)</h4>\n<ul><li>&quot;Year of Efficiency&quot; Airbnb-style: headcount cuts, marketing discipline</li><li>Net income $4.8bn (incluiu tax benefit one-off de $2.7bn) — operational underlying ~$2.1bn</li><li>Buyback $2.5bn iniciado de forma agressiva</li><li>Service fee structure changes (Pricing Display Worldwide rollout)</li></ul>\n<h4>FY24 (mid-cycle plateau + growth investments)</h4>\n<ul><li>Revenue +12%, EBITDA flat margin</li><li>Q4 24 Adj EBITDA margin 31%, depois caiu para 28% em Q4 25 — investment cycle</li><li>Pricing tools, Translation, Search improvements</li><li>FX headwind moderado</li></ul>\n<h4>FY25 (re-acceleration via product cycles + Services launch)</h4>\n<ul><li><strong>Maio/2025: Services + Experiences relaunch</strong> — Chesky chamado de &quot;biggest expansion since 2008 IPO of categories&quot; </li><li><strong>Reserve Now, Pay Later</strong> introduced em U.S. Q4 — <strong>&gt;70% adoption by eligible bookings em Q4!</strong> Driver de aceleração de Q4</li><li><strong>Hotels pilot</strong> em NYC, LA, Madrid, San Francisco — convert hotel demand para boutique/independent</li><li><strong>AI customer support rollout</strong> EN/FR/SP em US/CA/MX — <strong>~1/3 dos issues resolvidos sem agente humano</strong>, significant reduction in resolution time</li><li><strong>AI search</strong> começando rollout — natural language queries</li><li><strong>Geographic expansion</strong>: origin nights em &quot;expansion markets&quot; cresceram <strong>2x</strong> vs core markets<ul><li>Brasil, Japão: outperformance significativa</li><li><strong>India: first-time bookers +60% YoY</strong></li><li>Mexico, Korea: também strong</li></ul></li><li><strong>5 países = maioria do business</strong> — runway brutal em geographic expansion (220+ países atendidos)</li></ul>\n<h3>Take rate dynamics &amp; monetization (cuidadoso)</h3>\n<p><strong>Implied take rate FY25: 13.4%</strong> (Q4: 13.6%). <strong>Down YoY</strong> porque:</p>\n<ol><li>Mix shift cross-border (transactions com FX/insurance)</li><li>WHEN guests stay (timing of cash flow)</li><li><strong>Migração PMS hosts para fee unificado de 15.5%</strong> (started Oct/2025) — em vez de split 3% host + ~14% guest, agora single 15.5%</li><li>Most non-PMS hosts já estavam em single fee structure</li><li><strong>Guest travel insurance</strong>: introduced 2022, available em 12 dos top markets, growing adoption — incremental to take rate</li></ol>\n<p><strong>Implicação</strong>: ABNB está em transição de fee structure. <strong>Pode haver expansão modesta de take rate em 2026</strong> (Q1 26 mgmt guidance: &quot;implied take rate up slightly YoY&quot;).</p>\n<h3>Stock-based compensation</h3>\n<ul><li>FY25 SBC +13% YoY (driven by headcount growth)</li><li>2026: management espera <strong>growth rate of SBC and headcount lower than 2025</strong> — disciplina de capital allocation reforçada</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 — strategic narrative (shareholder letter + earnings call)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-08</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-shareholder-letter\">shareholder letter</a> (27 páginas) + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/ABNB/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FactSet Corrected Transcript</a> (07-May-2026, 20 páginas). Foco: <strong>strategic context</strong> que NÃO está no 10-Q financial detail.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 FY26 OUTLOOK RAISED — primeira vez em multi anos</strong></h3>\n<p>Mertz (CFO) na call:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;For the full year 2026, we now expect Nights and Seats Booked growth to <strong>accelerate to low-to-mid teens</strong>. The upward revision to our revenue outlook reflects meaningful progress across [...] our monetization initiatives, which are expected to lift our full year take rate.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;For 2026, we now expect our Adjusted EBITDA Margin to be <strong>at least 35%</strong>. We will continue to prioritize reinvestment to support growth across the business, specifically on efficient marketing spend, international expansion, and AI initiatives.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25 actual</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>FY26 outlook (raised)</strong></th><th>Implicação</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Nights &amp; Seats Booked YoY</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+8%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>low-to-mid teens (~12-15%)</strong></td><td><strong>Major acceleration</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Adj EBITDA Margin</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">35%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>≥ 35%</strong></td><td>flat-to-up despite reinvestment</td></tr><tr><td>Effective tax rate</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">20%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>high teens</strong></td><td>down (post-OBBBA + foreign earnings tax)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Drivers da raise (Mertz)</strong>:</p>\n<ol><li>Strong nights booked momentum (NA + LatAm fastest)</li><li>Slightly higher ADRs durability over the year</li><li>Monetization initiatives lifting full-year take rate (single fee migration, insurance, RNPL global)</li></ol>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Reserve Now, Pay Later (RNPL) — 20% do GBV global</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;In Q1, roughly <strong>20% of global GBV came from Reserve Now, Pay Later bookings</strong>. It&#x27;s one of the clearest examples of a change that [drives transformation].&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<ul><li>Q4 25 já era &gt;70% adoption no <strong>US</strong> (eligible bookings)</li><li>Q1 26: <strong>rolled out globally</strong>, agora <strong>~20% do GBV global</strong> vem de RNPL</li><li>Drives <strong>lead times longer</strong> + <strong>mix shift toward larger/higher-priced homes</strong></li><li>Material lift to gross bookings em <strong>todos os mercados</strong> testados</li><li><strong>Net positive impact</strong> depois de cancellation tests</li><li>US ainda highest adoption, outros mercados catching up</li><li>Mertz: &quot;we&#x27;re still in early innings... rolling out globally + bringing it to desktop + barely merchandising it&quot;</li><li>→ <strong>Path forward</strong>: more merchandising up-funnel + desktop + payment method localization</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 App-first strategy = strongest momentum in a decade</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>Q1 26</strong></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Δ</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>App nights booked YoY</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+22%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">acelerando</td></tr><tr><td>App % of total nights</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">58%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>63%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+5pp</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Brian: <em>&quot;It&#x27;s actually the strongest momentum we&#x27;ve seen in a decade.&quot;</em> Drivers: aggressive push notifications, email hooks, top free travel app rankings.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 First-time bookers +10% YoY = highest since Q1 2022</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Mercado</th><th>Métrica Q1 26</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Brazil origin nights</strong></td><td><strong>+22% YoY (3rd consecutive quarter)</strong> — agora consistently top-3-5 mercado (era barely top-10)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>India origin nights</strong></td><td><strong>+50% YoY</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Japan</strong></td><td>acelerando (high-single → high-teens nights growth)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>First-time bookers India</strong></td><td><strong>+75% YoY</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Net nights expansion markets</td><td><strong>+2x core markets</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Hyper-localization estratégia</strong>: 16 local marketing campaigns lançados em Q1 alone. Examples:</p>\n<ul><li>Italy: highlighting popular bed-and-breakfast displays</li><li>Germany: highlighting cleanliness (cultural priority)</li><li>Brazil: 2 anos de focused investment, agora payoff exponencial</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Major events strategy — Olympics + World Cup</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Olympic Games Milano Cortina 2026 (Q1):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>~200,000 guests stayed via Airbnb</li><li><strong>GBV more than tripling</strong> in Milan during games</li><li>Supply growth +30% in host markets</li><li>Validation of playbook</li></ul>\n<p><strong>FIFA World Cup 2026 (this summer) — &quot;largest event in Airbnb history&quot;:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>&gt;100,000 homes listed for first time</strong> across 16 host cities (3 countries)</li><li>Most bookings expected closer to event date (Olympics + Paris precedent)</li><li><strong>Paris precedent</strong>: 6 months pós-games, <strong>&gt;50% supply retention</strong> = supply is permanently incremental</li><li>Compounding benefits: brand awareness + supply growth + city/government policy relationships</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 AI metrics — quantificação inédita</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>1. AI Code Generation (operational efficiency):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>~60% of code authored by AI</strong> (vs ~30% industry average = <strong>2x</strong>)</li><li>Brian: &quot;speed is #1 characteristic of AI&quot;</li><li>New CTO: <strong>Ahmad</strong> (former leader of <strong>Meta Llama model</strong>) — major hire signaling AI-native infrastructure investment</li><li>&quot;One of the most sophisticated AI-native companies in tech stack&quot;</li></ul>\n<p><strong>2. AI Customer Support (bottom-funnel — quantified):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>40%+ resolution without human agent</strong> (up from ~33% Q4 25)</li><li>Significantly faster resolution times</li><li><strong>🔥 Cost-per-booking decreased ~10% YoY in Q1</strong> — first quantified P&amp;L impact</li><li>Brian: &quot;best AI self-solve in all of travel&quot;</li><li>Multi-lingual, 100+ policies, tens of thousands evolving conversations</li></ul>\n<p><strong>3. AI Mid-funnel (review summaries, search):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>AI summaries on listing pages</li><li>AI matching for search ranking + relevance</li><li>More features at <strong>May 20 Summer Release</strong></li></ul>\n<p><strong>4. AI Search (top-funnel — exploration):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Brian: <em>&quot;I don&#x27;t think anyone has figured out AI for travel or e-commerce yet&quot;</em></li><li>Critique of ChatGPT chatbot model — 4 problems:<ol><li>Too much text (LLMs return text, hard to compare)</li><li>No direct manipulation (can&#x27;t move price slider)</li><li>Comparison broken (3 options shown vs 50,000 in Paris)</li><li>&quot;Multiplayer&quot; — bookings have multiple guests, can&#x27;t share thread</li></ol></li><li>ChatGPT shut down 3rd-party apps March 2026 (Brian noted)</li><li>Foundation: clean data warehouse + Ahmad CTO hire + infrastructure-first</li><li><strong>Will see &quot;a lot of innovation around AI search&quot; next year</strong></li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Hotels strategy — depth &amp; scale ambition</strong></h3>\n<p>Mertz + Brian explicit:</p>\n<ul><li>Currently <strong>single-digit % of nights</strong> — &quot;barely entered this business&quot;</li><li><strong>All top-line metrics scaling</strong>: supply + bookings</li><li><strong>🔥 55% of hotel bookers come back to book a home</strong> (1-year window) = onboarding ramp</li><li>3 strategic reasons to scale hotels:<ol><li><strong>Market size</strong>: ABNB only ~2% of total accommodation TAM</li><li><strong>Trip-fit</strong>: covers segments where home isn&#x27;t right (last-minute, solo, business)</li><li><strong>Onboarding</strong>: brings new global travelers into Airbnb ecosystem</li></ol></li><li><strong>Hotels prefer Airbnb economics</strong>: ~30%+ lower commissions vs OTAs (BKNG/EXPE)</li><li><strong>Independents pressured to franchise</strong> because chains have loyalty programs → <strong>Airbnb can be alternative</strong> to franchising</li><li>Brian: <em>&quot;Hotels could be a multibillion-dollar revenue business without anyone intentionally coming to Airbnb to book a hotel&quot;</em> — leverage existing 2bn+ traffic</li><li>More updates <strong>May 20 Summer Release</strong></li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Delta Airlines partnership expanded</strong></h3>\n<ul><li>Delta miles agora em <strong>Experiences + Services</strong> (não só homes — <strong>3 miles per $1</strong> em Experiences/Services + <strong>1 mile per $1</strong> em homes)</li><li><strong>Revenue share program</strong> — não negative impact em take rate</li><li>Mertz: &quot;great opportunity to work with partners and effectively share in demand&quot;</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Brian on loyalty program (asked by Bernstein):</strong></p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;I&#x27;ve always believed the best loyalty program is people loving your product and coming back.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p><strong>No own loyalty program announced</strong> but: <em>&quot;when we do something, it will be truly differentiated and unique to Airbnb.&quot;</em></p>\n<p><strong>On flights</strong> (asked):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We don&#x27;t have any announcements... but it&#x27;s certainly on the table as part of our future vision.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Take rate dynamics — ALL drivers laid out</strong></h3>\n<p>Q1 26 implied take rate <strong>9.2%</strong> vs 9.3% Q1 25 (slight decrease) drivers:</p>\n<ul><li>FX timing</li><li>RNPL → guests book further in advance, payment timing shift</li><li><strong>PMS host migration to single 15.5% fee</strong> continuing — agora <strong>&gt;1/4 das active listings</strong> sob single fee</li><li><strong>Guest travel insurance revenue +45% YoY</strong> — material acceleration</li><li>Insurance available em <strong>12 largest countries</strong>, expanding</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Outlook FY26</strong>: take rate up YoY (single fee + insurance growth offset Delta partnership + insurance bookings timing)</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Capital structure — investment grade upgrade</strong></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>S&amp;P upgraded ABNB to investment grade</strong> (mentioned in call) — Moody&#x27;s also upgraded</li><li><strong>$2.5B unsecured senior notes issued at IG rates</strong> (4.40-5.25% blended ~5%)</li><li>First IG-rated debt — <strong>structural milestone</strong></li><li>Repaid $2.0B 0% convertibles → <strong>eliminates dilution risk</strong></li><li><strong>$500M extra cash retained</strong> for general corporate</li><li>Mertz: <em>&quot;This refinancing optimizes our long-term cost of capital&quot;</em></li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Amazon-as-inspiration framing — ecosystem strategy</strong></h3>\n<p>Brian (response to Brian Nowak/Morgan Stanley on ancillary revenue opportunities — air, car service, grocery, agentic):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;Is that too big? <strong>No. Definitely not.</strong> We are thinking very, very expansively... I do see Amazon as a pretty good inspiration for us.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p><strong>Strategy:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>&quot;We see ourselves building an <strong>ecosystem</strong>&quot;</li><li>Each new offering = <strong>less work than last</strong> (~10% different — efficiency compounding)</li><li>Different services bring different customer profiles</li><li><strong>Hybrid model</strong>: 1st party for differentiated offerings (ex: Services unique to host), 3rd party for efficient verticals (ex: groceries via <strong>Instacart partnership</strong>)</li><li>Implies coming verticals: <strong>air, car service, grocery, agentic experiences</strong></li><li>Brian: <em>&quot;We do really think this could be a generational business... think it&#x27;s just another inning&quot;</em></li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Q2 FY26 guidance specifics</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>Q2 26 guide</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue</td><td><strong>$3.04B</strong> (+14% to +16% YoY, incl ~3% FX tailwind after hedging)</td></tr><tr><td>Implied take rate</td><td>up slightly YoY</td></tr><tr><td>Nights &amp; Seats growth</td><td>slight deceleration vs Q1 (~100bps Middle East headwind)</td></tr><tr><td>Adj EBITDA + margin</td><td><strong>up YoY</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Macro / headwinds</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Middle East conflict ~100bps headwind</strong> to Nights &amp; Seats Q1 26 (without conflict, growth would be ~10% YoY vs reported 9%)</li><li>Q2 expected ~100bps similar headwind</li><li><strong>Tougher comp in H2</strong> vs RNPL rollout last year + Middle East</li><li>&quot;When tariff uncertainty resulted in fewer people traveling to US last year, they came to Airbnb and found somewhere else to go&quot; — <strong>flexibility most travel companies can&#x27;t replicate</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações materiais para tese (delta vs minha leitura prévia do 10-Q apenas)</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>FY26 raise é major signal</strong>: nights low-to-mid teens (vs FY25 +8%) é uma <strong>aceleração de 4-7pp</strong> no driver principal de revenue. Combined com take rate up = revenue growth bem acima dos +12% modelados FOX ✓ <strong>AI cost-per-booking -10% YoY</strong> = primeira quantificação concreta do AI ROI; reforça mid-term margin expansion thesis ✓ <strong>App 63% of nights + +22% YoY</strong> = direct traffic moat compoundando; less dependency on paid channels ✓ <strong>First-time bookers +10% (highest since Q1 22)</strong> = TAM expansion sinal forte (pré-cycle peak) ✓ <strong>Hotels potential &quot;multibillion dollar&quot;</strong> com 55% conversion home/hotel = optionality material não modelada ✓ <strong>S&amp;P IG upgrade + 0% converts retired</strong> = capital structure cleaning, sets up bigger M&amp;A optionality ⚠️ <strong>AI search ainda exploration mode</strong> — Brian explicit que &quot;no one figured it out&quot; → não é vetor de upside curto prazo ⚠️ <strong>Reinvestment vs margin</strong> trade-off explícito: Mertz disse Adj EBITDA margin <strong>at least 35%</strong> = não vai expandir muito vs FY25 (35%); reinvestment em marketing + intl expansion + AI absorvendo upside operativo</p>\n<h3>Cross-implications</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> — Brian explicit que ABNB usa <strong>Amazon as inspiration</strong> for ecosystem strategy. Não há ABNB→AMZN business linkage direta, mas frame estratégico.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> — ABNB AI customer support 40%+ resolution + cost-per-booking -10% = real-world validation de agentic AI ROI; AI search exploration consistent com &quot;agentic é early innings&quot;</li></ul></section>", "insider": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Insider Trading</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/ABNB.md</code>.</p></div>"}, "source": "wiki/ABNB.md", "built_at": "2026-06-09"};
